Some intellectual abilities do not decline with age, while other abilities decline at different rates. In general, verbal abilities tend to be maintained while psychomotor speed and problem solving tend to decline. Studies using the Wechler Adult Intelligence Scale (WAIS), indicated the elderly do best on information, vocabulary, and comprehension subtests; less well on arithmetic and picture completion subtests; and worst on tests of object assembly, block design, and picture arrangement.

