Second, in verbal learning-learning lists of words, for example, adults over 60 generally do not perform as well as do young adults, but experts are now debating whether these performance differences reflect real differences in learning ability. Some attribute the inferior performance of older adults to pacing problems. It is on timed tasks that older people perform most poorly.

